OL,3,C'All communities' want to see grooming
OL,4,Cgangs punished, says Council leader
OL,6,F"We apologise again to those who were
OL,7,Ffailed and thank the survivors who
OL,8,Fhave been bravely telling their
OL,9,Fstories to not let these injustices go
OL,10,Fforgotten.
OL,12,F"Baroness Casey has shone a bright
OL,13,Flight on uncomfortable and distressing
OL,14,Fissues that will now help us navigate
OL,15,Fa path to protect our children. Anyone
OL,16,Fwho cares about the safety of children
OL,17,Fshould read and digest this report.
OL,19,F"All agencies with responsibility for
OL,20,Fsafeguarding children should implement
OL,21,Fits recommendations in full."
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/13
